articles.description: The federal government has dropped charges against Jonathan Augustine, a former AAU basketball director from Florida, in the Adidas scandal case.
articles.headline: Feds drop charges against AAU basketball program director in Adidas scandal case

images.caption: Charges were dropped for a man accused of helping Adidas funnel money to families of high-ranked basketball recruits.
images.name: Adidas logo [600x400]

articles.description: Will Curry's incredible shooting become the new normal for more guards like the OU star? Kevin Pelton examines what Young shows about the NBA MVP's effect on future draft prospects.
articles.headline: Is Trae Young just the first of many Steph Curry clones?

images.caption: Oklahoma's breakout star Trae Young joins SC6 and says that he emulates different styles of players like Steph Curry and Steve Nash.
images.name: OU's Young has a fan in Curry

articles.description: The NCAA tournament selection committee released its initial top 16 seeds this weekend, which gave Bubble Watch a chance to clear a few teams off the bubble and into lock status.
articles.headline: Bubble Watch: Let's hand out some locks

images.name: Duke vs. North Carolina (Theo Pinson #1 of the North Carolina Tar Heels dunks the ball) [608x342]

articles.description: Trae Young's sudden struggles is the biggest question in the Big 12. In the SEC, it's a daily struggle for Kentucky. As March approaches, each league has some big things to figure out over the next two weeks.
articles.headline: The most important thing as conference play winds down

images.caption: This has not been an easy year for John Calipari and Kentucky.
images.name: Kentucky [608x342]

articles.description: It wasn't that long ago that Pitt was an NCAA tournament mainstay. Now, the Panthers are 0-13 in the ACC. Kevin Stallings thinks he can turn things around, but will he even get the chance?
articles.headline: What happened to Pitt basketball?

images.caption: Things are a mess at Pittsburgh. Is coach Kevin Stallings' run ending?
images.name: Kevin Stallings [1296x864]

articles.description: With both teams heading into the game looking for a much needed win, Baylor's Jo Lual-Acuil Jr. slams home the go-ahead dunk with 10 seconds left in double overtime to give the Bears a 74-73 victory.
articles.headline: Baylor edges Texas in 2OT thriller

videos.description: Devonte' Graham gets an offensive rebound and Sviatoslav Mykhailiuk finishes the play with a three.
videos.headline: Mykhailiuk capitalizes off turnover with 3-pointer

videos.description: Malik Newman drains a three to give the Jayhawks a solid lead on the Wildcats.
videos.headline: Newman's 3 gives Kansas early double-digit lead

videos.description: Sacha Killeya-Jones rejects Malik Newman's shot to prevent the Jayhawks from scoring.
videos.headline: Killeya-Jones comes up with big block

videos.description: Hamidou Diallo forces a turnover and then goes the other way for a dunk.
videos.headline: Diallo gets steal and slam

videos.description: Kentucky head coach John Calipari passionately explains that his team has to win the battle on the boards to get ahead of Kansas.
videos.headline: Calipari: 'If we don't rebound we have no chance of winning this game'

videos.description: Quade Green lobs a pass up for Hamidou Diallo who makes a tough lay-in.
videos.headline: Green connects with Diallo for alley-oop

videos.description: Hamidou Diallo takes advantage of the offensive rebound with a shot while getting the foul.
videos.headline: Diallo ties game with and-1

videos.description: Lagerald Vick throws a pass across the court and Sviatoslav Mykhailiuk slams it down for the Jayhawks.
videos.headline: Vick hauls pass to Mykhailiuk for a dunk

videos.description: Devonte' Graham elevates one for Udoka Azubuike to extend Kansas' lead.
videos.headline: Azubuike gets a slam on alley-oop

videos.description: Malik Newman drains a 3-pointer and the Jayhawks' bench is pumped up.
videos.headline: Newman hits wide-open three

videos.description: Devonte' Graham says his team was able to make tough plays which was key in their 65-61 win over Kentucky.
videos.headline: Graham says little things came together in win over Kentucky

videos.description: Kevin Knox leads all scorers with 20 points but the Wildcats suffer their first loss on the season in the State Farm Champions Classic.
videos.headline: No. 7 Kentucky comes up short vs. No. 4 Kansas 65-61

videos.description: It came down to the final minute, but Sviatoslav Mykhailiuk and No. 4 Kansas were able to hold off No. 7 Kentucky in a 65-61 victory.
videos.headline: Kansas squeaks by Kentucky in Champions Classic
